		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Robot Cars and Ethics
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1854127">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							It is an interesting question, but I think one overstated in the example. How would the car even identify that the thing in the road is a child? <br />
<br />
It would be expensive, but I've thought for awhile now that important roads should have an electronic element to them. The original idea was so that you could get early warning when emergency vehicles were coming up behind you (so you could pull off early), but it would also serve to provide more data to self-driving cars. In the above example, the car would know there was an obstruction in the road long before it became a dangerous situation. <br />
<br />
As for how the car is coded, it will probably boil down to liability before anything else. The company will have to take the route that is less likely to get them sued. I think they would have to only drive at speeds in which they can come to a full stop (without swerving) within their detection range. Buffers need to be programmed for other cars and for pedestrians, but otherwise protect the safety of the occupant. Pedestrians might need alternative systems developed for them, like separate walkways.<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
