			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Robot Cars and Ethics
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1854185">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Bonlainy</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=e45669a1bc6b2de5827f37bea1d046d3&amp;p=1854109#post1854109" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">[URL]<br />
I for one am really torn on the whole coming of the robot car.  On the one hand I would love an autopilot when I have to drive a long way on a boring interstate highway (although with audio books even that is no longer as bad as it use to be), but on the other hand (and I know you will be able to disengage autopilot mode) I love to drive on challenging, fun roads.  Driving is like a lot of other things in life, at times it's a chore, but often it can be freeing and fun.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>The ultimate solution is have areas that are autopilot only,  An example would be high traffic areas.  Driving about town, the freeway, grocery runs, kid pickup runs, work commute.  all things that are tedium and perfect for a computer.<br />
<br />
Eventually automatic drive on freeways could increase speed even with increasing density of traffic.<br />
<br />
Another place id target with auto drive is large campuses,  Personally if I were Google id be working with Disney right now.   Imagine someone being able to pop open an app on their phone and like Uber request a ride at their hotel in the Disney Resort Complex in Florida.  A Google Car would show up and take them to their location be it another hotel or one of the many parks in the WDW Resort.   The reason I suggest this location is that it is a moderately controlled environment,  But also the perfect setting to test the concept of the computer driven taxi.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
