			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Robot Cars and Ethics
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1854189">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							There was a stint that I did a few years ago on a business park that had self-driving cars. It was either walk, or use the self-driving cars. Those cars were doing just fine most of the time, unless when you needed them. In bad weather, rain, or heavy wind they would all but stop functioning because their sensors thought that large puddles, tree branches or whatever on the road might be people lying there. Couldn't drive around them either. Right now, they're like using horribly expensive matrix printers while a normal typewriter will do the job just fine.<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>FilanFyretracker</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=e45669a1bc6b2de5827f37bea1d046d3&amp;p=1854119#post1854119" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">This is also why I think freeways are the best place to allow automatic drive.  Let self driving cars use the HOV lanes in areas that have them.   There is maybe a 1% chance of a person being in the drive path on a freeway.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>By the time the technology is perfected, shouldn't it be the other way around? This &quot;kill-the-child-or-not?&quot; dilemma isn't caused by software, it's just one that software is now starting to address. At some point we'll probably come around to teaching them proper reaction (something like &quot;set off airbags, REALLY hit the brakes&quot; comes to mind), but by the time we've properly taught our cars that, would you really still want flesh-and-meat drivers around your kids' school?
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
