		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Robot Cars and Ethics
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1854194">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Etelka</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=e45669a1bc6b2de5827f37bea1d046d3&amp;p=1854189#post1854189" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">By the time the technology is perfected, shouldn't it be the other way around? This &quot;kill-the-child-or-not?&quot; dilemma isn't caused by software, it's just one that software is now starting to address. At some point we'll probably come around to teaching them proper reaction (something like &quot;set off airbags, REALLY hit the brakes&quot; comes to mind), but by the time we've properly taught our cars that, would you really still want flesh-and-meat drivers around your kids' school?</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I'm very much for self-driving cars, and really look forward to having one - many years into the future.<br />
Since I happen to live in a country that has an average 180 days of rain and snow per year, I'm not exactly jumping on the &quot;FIRST!&quot; bandwagon. There are still a lot of issues with sensors and precipitation.<br />
---<br />
But.<br />
Someone will get killed by a self-driving car. The situation in which they were killed, will be one that would possibly not have been fatal if it was a human driver.<br />
I don't have a handy example (like I said, I'm very much pro-selfdriving cars), but the media will be sure to write stuff like &quot;Died in a self-driving car accident! Would have lived if he/she had driven the car!&quot;.<br />
<br />
Compared to absolutely MINDBOGGLING number of people who die on a yearly basis in normal cars, this will be a fraction of a fraction of a decimal point.<br />
But it will create huuuuuuuuuuuge debates.<br />
<br />
And, like you guys said earlier: The whole &quot;Who's to blame&quot; hasn't been worked out, and is a hodgepodge of damages and lawyering that will take years and years and years to sort out.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
		        		<blockquote class="signature restore"><div class="signaturecontainer">&quot;Silver bullet solutions are rare, silver bullet sales commonplace&quot;</div></blockquote>
				
                                        
			</div>
			
