		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Robot Cars and Ethics
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1854239">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Someone said it above, but a car most likely won't be able to tell if an object in the way is a child, a small adult, or a big dog, nor would it be able to tell if the object is old or young, at least not early on, but eventually..............<br />
<br />
I do see where a &quot;robot car&quot; could cut down on fatalities, mostly because they would be programmed to follow traffic laws precisely, at least that's my guess.  To be honest, though, I an most up on exactly how they determine what traffic signs are along a route, or how they determine lanes when you can barely make out a dividing line, or where new construction is going on and the lines have yet to be painted.  I know that during a drive from here to LA on I-5 none of my stops are planned, so if all cars going down I-5 were self-driven and a &quot;passenger&quot; decides they want to take an exit at the last minute and get something to drink, that will definitely affect what happens to vehicles in other lanes and directly behind them.  Maybe this has all been worked out, but color me skeptical.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
