		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Robot Cars and Ethics
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1854295">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Schezar</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=e45669a1bc6b2de5827f37bea1d046d3&amp;p=1854270#post1854270" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Yuuuuup, no one will willingly pay for a product that will kill them to save someone else, regardless of circumstances. Nor should they. If you fall onto a highway the only person responsible for your subsequent death is you or whoever pushed you. RIP, kiddo. The only thing that would reduce accidental deaths of that nature would be to mandate high fences and walls blocking access to the freeways by pedestrians. That becomes a cost vs safety debate.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>fortunately I think at least with law they rarely ever fault a driver on a freeway for slamming a person.  Since the whole idea of the freeway is there are not supposed to be unwanted things like people trying to cross.   Usually the only time I see fault is if its a disabled vehicle and other drivers note things like its emergency blinkers were going.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
		        		<blockquote class="signature restore"><div class="signaturecontainer">&quot;When you name your baby Jeeves...you've pretty much set up his career for life. You don't see many Hit Men, for example, named Jeeves. &quot;Pardon me sir, but I must wack you now.&quot;<br />
— Jerry Seinfeld <br />
<br />
<font color="blue"><span style="font-family: Arial">Delmarva 85 Troll Enhancement Shaman Alternate Eclipse</span></font><br />
<br />
<font size="2">Never Forget those who gave it all ten years ago.</font></div></blockquote>
				
                                        
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
